ABUJA – The National Chairman of Labour Party, Julius Abure, on Thursday in Abuja declared that he was back as National Chairman, and that the LP was united and has no faction in its rank. He also disclosed that the suspended Deputy National Chairman of the party, Apapa Lamidi, failed in its attempt to create a faction in LP. Abure also revealed that the FCT High Court in Abuja ceases to have jurisdiction over a suit praying for a restraining order over him. The LP National Chairman who spoke in a press conference at the party’s Secretariat, told journalists that earlier restraint by the FCT High Court has been set aside by “our appeal at the Appeal Court ”. Details Soon.